title: SFH on dust explosion incident in Taiwan and MERS
content_text:
p>
	Following is the transcript of remarks made by the Secretary for Food and 
	Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, after attending a radio programme today (June 29): Reporter: (On why the Government does not consider a total ban on the party 
	spray.) Secretary for Food and Health: We are very concerned about the explosion 
	incident that happened in Taiwan. Unfortunately, there are at least five 
	Hong Kong citizens suffering different degrees of burns and injuries in this 
	incident. The Hong Kong Government and our medical system will do our best

incident. The Hong Kong Government and our medical system will do our best 
	to provide appropriate service to them. Regarding reports about two proposed 
	similar activities to be held in Hong Kong, the Food and Environmental 
	Hygiene Department (FEHD) will consider the advice from several relevant 
	government departments, including the Fire Services Department (FSD), before 
	issuing licences for these activities. FSD will consider a chain of factors, 
	including the scale and venue of the activity and the use of any combustible

including the scale and venue of the activity and the use of any combustible 
	materials or structures, in order to reach an advice for FEHD. Reporter: (On the Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MERS).) Secretary for Food and Health: Regarding the MERS, today is the second 
	consecutive day that Korea has reported zero confirmed cases. We started to 
	count a total of 28 days from yesterday onward to confirm whether 
	transmission in Korea has been terminated. We adopt a 28-day period, which

transmission in Korea has been terminated. We adopt a 28-day period, which 
	is equal to two cycles of incubation period, because there are exceptional 
	cases with incubation period longer than the usually reported 14 days. 
	Secondly, there are also other factors that we need to consider including 
	whether there are any people who have contracted the illness but have not 
	developed symptoms severe enough to be diagnosed as a case. Taking all these 
	factors into account, we consider that it is more prudent to use two cycles
factors into account, we consider that it is more prudent to use two cycles of incubation period as a standard. (Please also refer to the Chinese portion of the transcript.)
